value.0: "Hello! Dverin is out for the day and is only able to see people by appointment. What can I do for you this <quarterday>?"

"Oh my.  Are you an enterprising entrepreneur? Perhaps a purveyor of products or a trafficker in traded goods? A wholesaler of wholesome tinctures, or maybe you are an exporter of enchanted wares?" 
<StartAction>[She hummed thoughtfully.]</Start>
"Well, we wouldn't want you to be an illegitimate purveyor of illicit products, would we? Look no further, I have a merchanting license for you." 

"To register for shop ownership, there is a five-thousand Aenar charge. Not all shops require a merchanting license for you to hawk your wares, but this will ease the process across the county."
"Oh, you  want to rent a house?"

"Well, I still handle the paperwork, but we've simplified the process. Simply find a house that you like and have your first month's rent ready, settle in and when I do the morning rounds through the town, I'll be sure to make sure the amount will get withdrawn from your account with the Copriths."
<StartAction>[The woman smiles in a strange fashion.]</Start>"You get to find someplace else to live."
"Well, we can provide additional keys if you have multiple guests staying with you.  But, you'll have to wait for an appointment with Arkus. And your rent may increase."
"Hmm. Well, maybe that house just...isn't for you, hmm? We wouldn't want you to live above or below your means."
"Work? Hmm. I suppose you could always head west into the Duskwood. There are always nasty things to fight there."
"Well, you could always transport some goods if you're the merchantile sort. The Mayor is always looking for folks to venture out on the roads for it."

"Yes, transport. When you come across a hamlet or a guildhouse, you can purchase the goods they produce there. Then, you can bring them back here to the Ranger's Rest and sell them to us. Brost is also looking for other goods - berries, antidotes, iron - just about anything you can find we would like. So long as you have several."
"Oh? New to the county then? I'll need your name and...it is...<GameMonth>/<GameYear>..."
"You are now registered with the county. Is there anything else you need?"
[What happens when my account is empty?]
[I can't rent a house I like!]
[I need to register with the county.]
